{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7eee8175-ccb4-427e-80d5-b1c66fc0732e","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 **dropped support** for two of your three target frameworks:\n\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported (EOL)\n- **`net5.0`** — not supported (EOL)\n- **`net462`** — ✅ still supported (.NET Framework 4.6.2+)\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET Core side.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your targets, e.g., replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`) and `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0`. Then you can also simplify your package references — MSTest v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package replacing the separate `TestFramework` and `TestAdapter` packages.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"994b8261-7324-426a-8fc3-28f44ffbd058","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze the project:\n\n1. **Target frameworks**: `net5.0`, `net462`, `netcoreapp3.1`\n2. **Current MSTest version**: 2.2.10\n3. **Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk**: 17.5.0\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for:\n   - .NET Framework versions older than .NET Framework 4.6.2 — `net462` is exactly 4.6.2, so that should be fine.\n   - .NET Core 3.1 — this is a problem! `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported.\n   - .NET 5.0 — also no longer supported.\n\nSo upgrading to MSTest v3 would break compatibility with two of the three target frameworks since v3 requires .NET 6.0 or later for the .NET Core runtime.\n\n`net462` should work fine though, as MSTest v3 still supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+.\n\nOne other thing to note: MSTest v3 consolidated the package structure, so instead of needing both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`, there's now a single `MSTest` meta-package available, though the individual packages still exist if needed.","outputTokens":651,"requestId":"3402:15E90A:DB85A2:102478A:69F41220"},"id":"3a3c9b60-ab